#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
<h2 align=center>%%PRODUCT%% General Information</h2>
Welcome to %%PRODUCT%% where
<a href="Problems.cgi">everything just works</a> and it's obvious
<a href="Rollout.cgi">what to do</a>.
<p>As a driver, you'll find the following helpful:
    <ul>
	<li><a href="Driver.cgi">Routing software as a driver</a></li>
        <li><a href="Mobile_Internet_devices.cgi">%%MID%%s</a></li>
    </ul>

<p>As a coordinator or administrator, lots of help is available.  At least while you're learning
to use the software, we recommend using a browser with a multi-button mouse as right-clicking
on many things like buttons, pull-downs and fields gives you more information on what they
are used for.

<p>The software is quite usable on touch screens or with only single-button mice, but the help
facility is not accessed as easily.

<p>As a routing administrator, you'll be dealing with 4 types of records, the 4 principle types of
search and data entry menus:
    <ul>
	<li><a href="search_Distributor.cgi">Distributors</a>
	    - you'll only care about one</li>
	<li><a href="search_Staff.cgi">Staff</a>
	    - people who maintain the database and drive</li>
	<li><a href="search_Route.cgi">Routes</a>
	    - the routes they drive, originating and terminating at the distributor</li>
	<li><a href="search_Patron.cgi">Patrons</a>
	    - the people/places they drive to (the stops)</li>
    </ul>
In practice, you'll spend only enough time in the top level (Distributors) to get
to somewhere else.  
<p>You'll spend most of your time adding and modifying patrons, and somewhat less time,
modifying route orders.  

